to narratives of this period that have presented postmodernism as a question of style, as the methods and techniques traced here have been more deeply consequential than the many stylistic shifts of the past half century. Sean Keller closes the book with an analysis of the contemporary condition, suggesting future paths for architectural practice that work through, but also beyond, the merely automatic.    aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 22. Okt 2019) 0aArchitectural designxHistoryy20th century. 0aArchitectural designxPhilosophy. 0aArchitecture, Moderny20th century. 0aArchitecture, Postmodern. 4aarchitecture. 4aautomatic. 4apostwar. 70(DE-601)1042803520(DE-588)4002851-3aArchitektur2gnd 70(DE-601)1046232840(DE-588)4130545-0aAutorschaft2gnd 70(DE-601)1046587110(DE-588)4039827-4aModerne2gnd 70(DE-601)1058361090(DE-588)4112587-3aArchitekturtheorie2gnd 70(DE-601)1063524660(DE-588)4011510-0aDesign2gnd 70(DE-601)1063882070(DE-588)4003957-2aAutomation2gnd 7aARCHITECTURE / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019z978311063851608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018z978311063537940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226496528423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780226496528.jpg  a978-3-11-063537-9  University of Chicago Press eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-063851-6  DG and UP eBook Package 2016-2019c2016d2019  aGBV-deGruyter-alles